              }
            },
            {
              "@type": "Question",
              "name": "What is the role of Section 56(2)(viib) when the holding subscribes to SPV shares?",
              "acceptedAnswer": {
                "@type": "Answer",
                "text": "Section 56(2)(viib) of the Income-tax Act treats any premium received above fair market value as income in the hands of the SPV when shares are issued to residents. To pre-empt the risk, a valuation under Rule 11UA of the Income-tax Rules is commissioned before allotment using DCF or NAV method. The valuation aligns the subscription price with fair market value so the premium component falls within the safe-harbour and is not treated as income. For shares issued to non-residents, the FEMA pricing guidelines under FEMA (Non-Debt Instruments) Rules, 2019 govern the floor."
              }
            }
