<p>The structure rides on five statutes - the Companies Act 2013 (Section 2(46) holding, Section 2(87) subsidiary, Section 129(3) consolidation, Section 186 inter-corporate cap, Section 188 related-party); the Income-tax Act (Section 80M dividend deduction, Section 115BAA 22 percent concessional rate, Section 56(2)(viib) premium check, Section 92E transfer pricing); SEBI AIF and REIT regulations; FEMA inbound under FEMA (Non-Debt Instruments) Rules 2019; FEMA outbound under FEMA (Overseas Investment) Rules 2022. Patron Accounting LLP (15+ years and 10,000+ clients) designs and implements these structures from its Sector 48 Gurugram office, mapping each entity to a tax election, a Section 186 ceiling, a related-party-transaction discipline under Section 188, and an exit waterfall via Section 248(2) - starting INR 24,999 (Exl GST and Govt. Charges).</p>
